
<purchabr>BELL GROUP</purchabr> CONFIRMS <acqabr>STANDARD CHARTERED</acqabr> STAKE
    PERTH, April 8 - The <purchaser>Bell Group Ltd</purchaser> {<purchcode>BLLA.S</purchcode>} said it now
holds 14.9 pct of the issued capital of <acquired>Standard Chartered Plc</acquired>
{<acqcode>STCH.L</acqcode>} after acquiring further shares.
    The one-sentence statement from <purchabr>Bell</purchabr>'s headquarters
confirmed what its brokers Warburg Securities told Reuters in
London yesterday.
    <purchabr>Bell</purchabr> previously held 10 pct of <acqabr>Standard</acqabr>.
    <purchabr>Bell</purchabr> chairman Robert Holmes a Court, who is also a director
of <acqabr>Standard</acqabr>, was not available for comment on his company's
intentions in boosting its holding and other company officials
contacted here by Reuters declined to comment.
